TI  - Economic impact of COVID-19 across national boundaries: The role of government responses
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 1278
EP  - 1297
VL  - 54
IS  - 7
AB  - This Research Note provides an assessment of the burgeoning interdisciplinary literature surrounding the COVID-19 pandemic and its impact on both individuals and firms, with a particular focus on the heterogeneity in government responses and their implications for international finance and IB research. In particular, we discuss disparities in vaccine distribution, government policy responses, and impacts in low-income versus high-income countries, as well as lessons learned from the pandemic. We describe an important source of data in this area and provide ideas for future research.
